abstract: Eyong Tarkang Enoh (born 23 March 1986 in Kumba, Southwest Region, Cameroon) is a Cameroonian football midfielder who currently plays in the Süper Lig for Antalyaspor on loan from AFC Ajax, and for the Cameroon national team. He is the vice-captain of the Cameroon national team, alongside Nicolas N'Koulou. Both vice-captains deputise the skipper Samuel Eto’o.
